
setup new server:
$ sudo adduser luke
$ sudo usermod -a -G sudo luke
#admin privledges
$ gpasswd -a luke sudo

setup internet

The 198.23.162.64/29 has 5 usable IP's, which are:
Main IP: 198.23.162.66
Usable IP's:
198.23.162.67
198.23.162.68
198.23.162.69
198.23.162.70
Also, here is the additional info you'll need.
Gateway: 198.23.162.65
Netmask: 255.255.255.248
You can configure the rest of the IP's by following this simple guide:
https://www.2daygeek.com/how-to-add-additional-ip-secondary-ip-in-ubuntu-debian-system/

Here is the networking info you will need to set up the basic network.
IP Range: 198.23.162.64/29     
Main IP: 198.23.162.66
Gateway: 198.23.162.65
Subnet: 255.255.255.248
$
sudo ifconfig eno1 198.23.162.66 netmask 255.255.255.248
sudo ifconfig eno1 198.23.162.64/29 netmask 255.255.255.248
sudo route add default gw 198.23.162.65 eno1

sudo nano /etc/network/interfaces

auto lo eno1
iface lo inet loopback
iface eno1 inet static
        address 198.23.162.66
        netmask 255.255.255.248
        gateway 198.23.162.65
$
sudo /etc/init.d/networking restart




to set up a desktop environment:
https://www.techrepublic.com/article/how-to-install-the-gnome-desktop-on-ubuntu-server-18-04/
$ 
sudo apt-get install tasksel -y
sudo tasksel
#Once you've selected Ubuntu desktop, click the spacebar to select it, tab down to Ok, and hit Enter on your keyboard
$
reboot

